If you&#39;re using ActiveMQ Artemis with Spring-boot and Apache Camel you can use 

```xml
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.camel.springboot&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;camel-jms-starter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-artemis&lt;/artifactId&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

Then you can add following properties to your `application.properties` and `spring-boot-starter-artemis` should create you a connection factory with given settings. 


**Example application.properties:**

```bash
spring.artemis.mode=native
spring.artemis.host=localhost
spring.artemis.port=PORT
spring.artemis.user=username
spring.artemis.password=Password
```

If you&#39;re using the older ActiveMQ then you can use the `spring-boot-starter-activemq`

```xml
&lt;!-- according to the documentation camel-jms should work as well --&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.camel.springboot&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;camel-activemq-starter&lt;/artifactId&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.boot&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;spring-boot-starter-activemq&lt;/artifactId&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
```

**Example application.properties:**

```bash
spring.activemq.broker-url=tcp://localhost:PORT
spring.activemq.user=username
spring.activemq.password=Password
```

You can find more about spring-boot and jms using ActiveMQ and ActiveMQ Artemis from the [documentation](https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/2.0.x/reference/html/boot-features-messaging.html#boot-features-jms)

